OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FShoppers shun Christmas    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fsales as footfall drops    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Famid Covid fears           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The number of people taking advantage  
OL,6, of post-Christmas sales on Monday fell 
OL,7, by 37.2% compared with 2019, new data  
OL,8, shows, amid persistent Covid concerns. 
OL,10,FRetail analyst Springboard said        
OL,11,Ffootfall figures, up to midday, were   
OL,12,Fbetter than Boxing Day.                
OL,14,FBut popular shopping destinations such 
OL,15,Fas central London saw a drop caused in 
OL,16,Fpart by disruption to rail services.   
OL,18,FShoppers chose to visit retail parks on
OL,19,FMonday, but footfall there was still   
OL,20,Fdown 10.9% from pre-pandemic levels.   
